==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nauseous
<hw>Nau"seous</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nauseosus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Causing, or fitted to
cause, nausea; sickening; loathsome; disgusting; exciting abhorrence;
<as>as, a <ex>nauseous</ex> drug or medicine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Feeling nausea; <as>as, <ex>nauseous</ex> from the
effects of chemotherapy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Nau"seous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Nau"seous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>nauseousness</qex> of such company disgusts a reasonable
man.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nautch</ent>⟦br⟧
